                  <pb n="2"/>
                  <lb/>
best actions there is some remedy of<lb/>
corruption as wee <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> them: for the<lb/>
which God in <normalised orig="iustice" auto="true">justice</normalised> may <normalised orig="condemne" auto="true">condemn</normalised><lb/>
both <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> and our actions: for the<lb/>
Scripture <normalised orig="sayth" auto="true">saith</normalised>: <quote type="biblical" ana="Isa 64.6">That our very <normalised orig="righteousnesse" auto="true">righteousness</normalised><lb/>
is as a defiled <normalised orig="cloath" auto="true">cloth</normalised>, or filthy<lb/>
<normalised orig="cloute" auto="true">clout</normalised>.</quote> If then our best <normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised> <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised><lb/>
