            <sp who="b">
               <p>Child.<lb/>
                  <lb/>
Not so for although wee can not<lb/>
<normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> <normalised orig="iustified" auto="true">justified</normalised> in the sight of God by our<lb/>
good works: yet they <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> their necessary<lb/>
<normalised orig="vse" auto="true">use</normalised>, and <normalised orig="serue" auto="true">serve</normalised> to great purpose.<lb/>
As first to <normalised orig="glorifie" auto="true">glorify</normalised> God. Secondly,<lb/>
to publish our Faith to the<lb/>
world. Thirdly, to bring peace and<lb/>
comfort to our consciences in the discharge<lb/>
of our duties. And lastly, to<lb/>
<normalised orig="winne" auto="true">win</normalised> others.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Father.<lb/>
What <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> you call a good <normalised orig="worke" auto="true">work</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
